---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Waitlist from '../components/sections/Waitlist.astro';
import WaitlistForm from '../components/forms/WaitlistForm.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Couples Food System" description="Our story — why we built Couples Food System and our mission to remove the mental load of meal planning." version="v1">
  <section class="py-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-6">Our Story</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Brand Story Image -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg border border-border mb-12">
      <img src="/images/hero/about-story.webp" alt="A couple's hands preparing fresh vegetables together on a wooden table in a sun-drenched kitchen with sage green and terracotta accents" class="w-full h-auto" decoding="async" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 md:p-16 rounded-2xl border border-border shadow-sm space-y-6 text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        It started in our own kitchen. I wanted to lean out, and my partner wanted to build muscle. Suddenly, Sunday meal prep became a nightmare of two different recipes, two grocery lists, and twice the cleanup.
      </p>
      <p>
        We tried standard meal planning apps, but they felt clinical, isolating, and completely ignored the fact that cooking together is supposed to be a bonding experience, not a math equation.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's why we built <strong class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Couples Food System</strong>. We believe that sharing a meal is a cornerstone of a healthy relationship. Our mission is to remove the mental load of meal planning and the friction of dietary differences, so you can get back to what matters: enjoying dinner together.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem We Saw -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-text-primary">The Problem We Saw</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Mental Load</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary">One person carries the entire burden of meal planning, grocery lists, and dinner decisions. It's invisible work that creates resentment over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Dietary Divide</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary">When partners have different goals, they cook separately. Two meals, two grocery lists, twice the dishes. The shared kitchen becomes two solo kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Decision Fatigue</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary">"What's for dinner?" is the question that starts the stress cycle every evening. 20 minutes of scrolling, still no answer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Waste</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary">$600/year lost to duplicate purchases and forgotten ingredients. Not just money — it's the frustration of watching food go bad.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Our Solution -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-text-primary">Our Solution</h2>
      <div class="bg-sage/10 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-border">
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Couples Food System is the first app built from the ground up for two people sharing one kitchen. Instead of "track your calories," we ask "what are WE eating tonight?" Instead of browsing recipes for one person, we generate meals that work for both.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The result: one cooking session, two perfectly portioned plates, zero arguments. The food is just the medium — what we're really selling is less stress, fewer decisions, smoother evenings, and shared responsibility.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why Couples Food System -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-text-primary">Why Couples Food System?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We're not building another meal planning app. We're creating a new category: <strong class="text-text-primary">Collaborative Adaptive Nutrition</strong>. No competitor combines real-time collaboration, adaptive portions, pantry-first AI, and relationship-first design into one system. The center of the market is empty — and we're filling it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Waitlist>
    <WaitlistForm />
  </Waitlist>
</BaseLayout>
